name: Styrofoam® HL
description: Styrofoam® HL is an extruded Polystyrene foam used as insulation where high load-bearing is required. (Highload 40 - 60 - 100). It is a Type V extruded polystyrene foam insulation which resists compressive creep and fatigue, delivering long-term compressive strength and thermal performance in HL applications. Typical plank size is 2″ x 48″ x 96″ and is a blue material. It has a R-value of 10.
